1.1 Construct the model Features selected with both BARS and Permutation Importance

Code 
barsAccPlot, barsQQPlot, barsPiPlot, barsMach = modelPredictions(barsdf,targetVar," ",propertynames(barsdf),modelType,test,train)
import MLJDecisionTreeInterface

1.2 Accuracy

There is a slight improvement in training \(R^2\), but the most noticeable improvement is in the testing RMSE: this verifies that our feature selection method produces more accurate and interpretable models. Of course the problematic region from 700-800 ppm still exists, but there is less deviation from the 1:1 line at values above 700 ppm which indicates that this model generalizes better than the model which had all 329 biometric features present.

Code 
barsAccPlot

1.3 Quantile-Quantile

The Quantile-Quantile plot still looks fantastic below 700ppm; there is an improvement in the 700-900 range as well. The distributions more closely match one another which indicates that this model has done a better job learning the entire empirical distribution and not just the central tendency. This is another confirmation that our model has generalized to new data.

Code 
barsQQPlot

1.4 Permutation Importance

The relative permutation importances have balanced out: this indicates that each feature is contributing roughly the same amout to the predictive capability. This is an essential feature of a good model because we dont features which dont pull their weight or actively harm the model to stick around.

Code 
barsPiPlot
